						               													<description>Roc&amp;oacute;dromo is a climbing game for 2-4 players, 7+ years old and about 10 minutes of playing time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Roc&amp;oacute;dromo is a game in which we compete to be the first to reach the top of a climbing wall. As if it was a race, we combine colour sticks of different lengths which simulate the routes of the wall that was built at the beginning of the game. Who will be the first to conquer the climbing wall?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Roc&amp;oacute;dromo has two game modes: Basic and Advanced. The differences between them are the difficulty and the levels of the wall that we set to climb: &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     In Basic mode, the wall to be climbed will have three levels. &amp;#10;     In Advanced mode, the wall can have more levels, a different shape or it can include some special settings. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If it&amp;rsquo;s the first time you play, we recommend the Basic mode; once you know the mechanics, we encourage you to follow the rules to set up the game in Advanced mode.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
